#: ../../M/mainframe.rst:5
msgid "mainframe"
msgstr "mainframe"

#: ../../M/mainframe.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../M/mainframe.rst:9
msgid ""
"Term originally referring to the cabinet containing the central processor "
"unit or ‘main frame’ of a room-filling :ref:`Stone-Age` batch machine. After"
" the emergence of smaller minicomputer designs in the early 1970s, the "
"traditional :ref:`big-iron` machines were described as ‘mainframe computers’"
" and eventually just as mainframes. The term carries the connotation of a "
"machine designed for batch rather than interactive use, though possibly with"
" an interactive timesharing operating system retrofitted onto it; it is "
"especially used of machines built by IBM, Unisys, and the other great "
":ref:`dinosaur`\\s surviving from computing's :ref:`Stone-Age`\\."
msgstr ""
"元々は、部屋を埋め尽くす\\ :ref:`Stone-Age`\\ のバッチ機械の中央処理装置すなわち‘main "
"frame’を収める筐体を指す語。1970年代初頭により小型のミニコンピュータ設計が登場したのち、伝統的な\\ :ref:`big-iron`\\ "
"の機械は‘mainframe "
"computer’、やがて単にmainframeと呼ばれた。この語は、対話的な使用ではなくバッチ向けに設計された機械(ただしおそらく対話的なタイムシェアリングオペレーティングシステムが後付けされている)という含みを持つ。特にIBM、Unisys、そしてコンピューティングの\\"
" :ref:`Stone-Age`\\ から生き延びた他の偉大な\\ :ref:`dinosaur`\\ たちが製造した機械について使われる。"

#: ../../M/mainframe.rst:13
msgid ""
"It has been common wisdom among hackers since the late 1980s that the "
"mainframe architectural tradition is essentially dead (outside of the tiny "
"market for :ref:`number-crunching` supercomputers having been swamped by the"
" recent huge advances in IC technology and low-cost personal computing. The "
"wave of failures, takeovers, and mergers among traditional mainframe makers "
"in the early 1990s bore this out. The biggest mainframer of all, IBM, was "
"compelled to re-invent itself as a huge systems-consulting house. (See "
":ref:`dinosaurs-mating` and :ref:`killer-micro`\\)."
msgstr ""
"mainframeアーキテクチャの伝統は本質的に死んでいるというのが、1980年代後半以来ハッカーの間の通念である(\\ :ref:`number-"
"crunching`\\ "
"スーパーコンピュータのための小さな市場を除いて。それもIC技術と低コストのパーソナルコンピューティングの最近の巨大な進歩に飲み込まれた)。1990年代初頭の伝統的なmainframeメーカーの間の失敗、買収、合併の波がこれを裏付けた。すべてのmainframeメーカーの中で最大のIBMは、巨大なシステムコンサルティングハウスとして自己を再発明せざるを得なかった。(\\"
" :ref:`dinosaurs-mating`\\ と\\ :ref:`killer-micro`\\ を参照。)"

#: ../../M/mainframe.rst:18
msgid ""
"However, in yet another instance of the :ref:`cycle-of-reincarnation`\\, the"
" port of Linux to the IBM S/390 architecture in 1999 — assisted by IBM — "
"produced a resurgence of interest in mainframe computing as a way of "
"providing huge quantities of easily maintainable, reliable virtual Linux "
"servers, saving IBM's mainframe division from almost certain extinction."
msgstr ""
"しかし、\\ :ref:`cycle-of-reincarnation`\\ のさらにもう一つの例において、1999年のLinuxのIBM "
"S/390アーキテクチャへの移植は——IBMの支援を受けて——、容易に保守できる信頼性の高い仮想Linuxサーバーを大量に提供する方法としてmainframeコンピューティングへの関心の再燃を生み、IBMのmainframe部門をほぼ確実な絶滅から救った。"
